      "content": "I can see why you'd want to try a natural approach, but I'm not convinced that manuka honey alone will be enough to stop the bleeding and promote healing. You're right to clean the wound first, but applying a thick layer of honey may not provide enough pressure to stop the bleeding, and it's also a breeding ground for bacteria. I'd still recommend applying an antibiotic ointment to the wound, then covering it with a breathable dressing, and keeping a close eye on it. If the bleeding doesn't stop or you notice signs of infection, you may still need to seek medical attention.",
