      "content": "okay but the edges are definitely gaping open. if i use the honey to seal it and then wrap it really tight with some medical tape or a bandage, wouldn't that basically act like a temporary closure until it scabs over? i've seen people do this for much smaller cuts and it works fine. if i do that, do i really need to go in for stitches or can i just wait a day or two to see if it stays closed?",
